BOSTON -- Kelly Olynyk understands the Boston Celtics' salary-cap situation will loom over his restricted free agency this summer, but said he will not worry about how the team's pursuit of top targets could impact his future.

"It is what it is," Olynyk said Thursday afternoon after appearing at a Shamrock Foundation carnival for students who achieved perfect attendance throughout the school year, boosted their grades considerably or won one of the Celtics' annual writing or art contests.
